cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DM, cs.CE, cs.DB

This paper involves the development and training of a decision tree algorithm for predicting dengue fever based on clinical and laboratory data. This falls under the category of machine learning and data mining, which is covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DM (Data Mining). The use of decision trees also involves artificial intelligence, which is covered by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of data, which falls under the category of databases, covered by cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper involves the development of a predictive model for a disease, which falls under the category of computational epidemiology, covered by cs.CE (Computational Epidemiology).
